Package: h5lite
Title: Simplified 'HDF5' Interface
Version: 2.0.0.0
Authors@R:
    person("Daniel P.", "Smith", , "dansmith01@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A user-friendly interface for the 'HDF5' library designed to "just work." It bundles the necessary system libraries to ensure easy installation on all platforms. Features smart defaults that automatically map R objects (vectors, matrices, data frames) to efficient 'HDF5' types, removing the need to manage low-level details like dataspaces or property lists. Uses the 'HDF5' library developed by 'The HDF Group' <https://www.hdfgroup.org/>.
URL: https://github.com/cmmr/h5lite, https://cmmr.github.io/h5lite/
BugReports: https://github.com/cmmr/h5lite/issues
Depends: R (>= 4.2.0)
LinkingTo: hdf5lib (>= 2.0.0.5)
Suggests: bit64, knitr, rmarkdown, testthat (>= 3.0.0)
NeedsCompilation: yes
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Config/Needs/website: rmarkdown
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
VignetteBuilder: knitr
